      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KNOWING LOOK (3) scored a game win first-up at Newcastle then was 39 days between runs when a tiring sixth over 1400m at Hawkesbury last start. Will tighten right up with that last run under the belt and getting out to the mile should suit her down to the ground. MILES OF GLORY (4) has progressed at each appearance this time in work. Stepped up to 1600m for the first time recently at Gosford and handled it well, beaten just a long neck after racing on the speed. Very fit and capable of taking this out. VLTAVA (2) swept home from near the tail for an impressive maiden win over 1500m at Newcastle last time out. Going extra well since a change in stables this prep. Can play a key role again. SUNSET BELLE (5) had to pull out all stops to collect her maiden over this course and distance last start. Needs to raise the bar but looks up to the task. SOX (6) is very fit and can sneak into the frame without surprising.",
